00:38:07.089 --> 00:38:13.700
motivated actors from having, having publically
accessible speech without, without national

00:38:13.700 --> 00:38:19.789
control, which I think is something I think
we should be skeptical about. Where I think

00:38:19.789 --> 00:38:26.460
this is going is, is what Bob Axelrod showed
in his prisoner's dilemma work, the original

00:38:26.460 --> 00:38:32.789
sort of computer modeling of just very simple
interaction patterns, which is that small

00:38:32.789 --> 00:38:38.769
groups of cooperating actors can actually
build an environment for themselves inside

00:38:38.769 --> 00:38:42.859
a larger hostile environment in which, in
which value is possible.

00:38:42.859 --> 00:38:50.690
