that, or it could say it has one particular,
one particular place there. To take, to take

00:50:23.309 --> 00:50:28.249
just the example from here, right, Nisha Susan
used the network to coordinate people to take

00:50:28.249 --> 00:50:33.779
real world, to take real world action. The
one thing I will say about social networks

00:50:33.779 --> 00:50:40.490
is that our bias, you know, technologically
our bias for the last, you know, few decades,

00:50:40.490 --> 00:50:45.359
has been to lower the cost of messaging, right?
And, and it's had all of these wonderful effects

00:50:45.359 --> 00:50:50.310
that we've seen, but that around political
speech, low cost messaging has actually become

00:50:50.310 --> 00:50:51.349
a problem, right?

00:50:51.349 --> 00:50:56.599
We now, you know, campaigns are routinely
conducted to affect the business of the US

00:50:56.599 --> 00:51:01.580
Congress, which are conducted on the McDonald's
